Former Senator Jim Jeffords of Vermont passed away. Vice President Joe Biden and Dr. Jill Biden released a statement expressing their sadness and remembering Jeffords as a personal friend, a great senator, and a good man. They described him as beloved by the people of Vermont and anyone who worked with him. Jeffords was known for his commitment to consensus and solving problems, and he approached his colleagues with honesty and without pretext. The Bidens joined Jeffords' family, friends, and former staff in honoring his legacy of basic fairness and principled independence.